## âœ… What is Java Collections Framework?

Java Collections Framework is a **set of classes and interfaces** that provide **ready-made data structures** to store, manipulate, and access groups of objects efficiently.

It supports operations like **searching, sorting, insertion, deletion, and updating**.

---

## ðŸ”¹ Interfaces in Collections Framework:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Interface     |              Description                                   |
|---------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| `Collection`  | Root interface for most collection classes                 |
| `List`        | Ordered collection, allows duplicates                      |
| `Set`         | Unordered collection, no duplicates                        |
| `Queue`       | Used to hold elements before processing                    |
| `Deque`       | Double-ended queue (insert/remove from both ends)          |
| `Map`         | Key-value pairs (not a true child of Collection interface) |
| `SortedSet`   | Set with sorted elements                                   |
| `NavigableSet`| SortedSet with navigation methods                          |
| `SortedMap`   | Map with sorted keys                                       |
| `NavigableMap`| SortedMap with navigation support                          |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---

